. Furthermore, we show that any circuit that normalizes the stabilizer of\nthe code can be transformed into a circuit that centralizes the stabilizer,\nwhile realizing the same logical operation. Our method of circuit synthesis can\nbe applied to any stabilizer code, and this paper discusses a proof of concept\nsynthesis for the $[\\![ 6,4,2 ]\\!]$ CSS code. Programs implementing the\nalgorithms in this paper, which includes routines to solve for binary\nsymplectic solutions of general linear systems and our overall LCS (logical\ncircuit synthesis) algorithm, can be found at:\nhttps://github.com/nrenga/symplectic-arxiv18a\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 30 Jun 2019 03:22:02 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 18 Aug 2021 19:32:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-08-20"}
